snippet.textDisplay:
1: Children should be trusted to make their own decisions.
I think that kids should only be allowed to make their own decisions when they've reached a certain age. As long as you're living under my roof and using my money, any major decisions you make has to go through me first because I don't want my kids buying a freaking Tesla or joining a gang and getting in trouble. Of course things like choosing an ambition or deciding what to wear should be completely up to the child. I want to teach my kids independence through all these small decisions they make before releasing them into the world to finally choose the life they want.
2: Kids deserve privacy.
Of course. I want my kids to be able to write down their thoughts and secrets without the fear of someone reading it and to teach them to respect the privacy of others as well. I know that I've had a few embarassing moments in my life that I'd rather not tell anyone about. But that doesn't mean I want my children to keep EVERYTHING from me. If crazy things are going on in their lives or if they're going through depression or something, then I want them to be able to confide in me. I would show them that they can trust me and that I care about them so that they can tell me their problems on their own conditions, instead of forcing the truth out of them or make them feel pressured into talking to me.
3: Parents should be parents and not friends.
I agree with this. To me, being a parent comes first no matter the circumstance. I do not want my child to think that it's okay to disrespect me or mess around with me like I'm another kid. I want them to know that I'm not just there to play with them, but because I have authority over them and will be the one who has to deal with all of their rubbish for the next 18 years and hence should be treated with respect. Of course I would want a good, healthy relationship with my child, just not a "friendship".
4: Spanking your child is an acceptable form of punishment.
I feel like spanking your kids shouldn't be the first solution as there are many other ways to discipline a child without involving violence. However, I definitely think that it should be a last resort if all other methods fail.
